{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Event Kit and Event Kit UI frameworks together allow iPhone OS applications to access event information from a user’s Calendar database. You can fetch events based on a date range or a unique identifier, receive notifications when event records change, and allow users to create and edit events for any of their local and server-based calendars. Learn techniques to take advantage of these features and other useful tips from Apple engineers."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC10","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Calendar Integration with Event Kit","role":"sampleCode"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-136-calendar-integration-with-event-kit"]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/136\/","isActive":true}},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-136-Calendar-Integration-with-Event-Kit"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"references":{"WWDC10-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifi